MapReduce Program to Find Grades of Students
Theory (Write in Exam)
Introduction

MapReduce is a programming model used for processing large amounts of data in distributed systems such as Hadoop.

It works in two phases:

Mapper Phase
Reducer Phase

This program is used to calculate the grades of students based on their marks.

Problem Statement

Develop a MapReduce program to assign grades to students according to their marks.

Grade Criteria
Marks Range	Grade
90 – 100	A
75 – 89	B
60 – 74	C
40 – 59	D
Below 40	F
Working of Program
Mapper Phase
Reads student name and marks.
Determines grade based on marks.
Emits student name and grade.

Example:

Shyam    A
Reducer Phase
Collects mapper output.
Displays final student grades.
Advantages
Fast processing of student records.
Can handle large educational datasets.
Parallel execution improves performance.
Mapper Program (Python)
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import sys

for line in sys.stdin:
    line = line.strip()

    # Input format:
    # Name,Marks

    name, marks = line.split(',')

    marks = int(marks)

    # Assign grades
    if marks >= 90:
        grade = 'A'
    elif marks >= 75:
        grade = 'B'
    elif marks >= 60:
        grade = 'C'
    elif marks >= 40:
        grade = 'D'
    else:
        grade = 'F'

    print(f"{name}\t{grade}")
Reducer Program (Python)
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import sys

for line in sys.stdin:
    line = line.strip()

    name, grade = line.split('\t')

    print(f"{name}\t{grade}")
